# Backend Conventions

## Stack
- Node.js + Express, PostgreSQL (production) / SQLite (local dev)
- Stripe for payments, Resend for transactional emails
- Session-based auth (express-session) with bcrypt PIN hashing

## Database
- Query wrappers: `query()`, `queryOne()`, `execute()` from `config/database.js`
- Use `$1, $2` parameterized placeholders (PostgreSQL style); the wrapper auto-converts for SQLite
- `initConnection()` must be called before queries (handled by server startup; standalone scripts use `pg.Pool` directly)
- Tables: `users`, `orders`, `addons`, `products`, `admins`, `email_logs`, `ebook.download_events`

## Auth
- User auth: email + OTP or PIN (4-digit bcrypt hash in `users.pin_hash`)
- Admin auth: `requireAdmin` middleware checks `req.session.adminId`
- User auth: `requireAuth` middleware checks `req.session.userId`

## Orders
- `orders.new_addons` and `orders.shipping_address` are JSON strings stored in TEXT columns
- `payment_status` values: `pending`, `card_saved`, `succeeded`, `charged`, `charge_failed`
- `paid` column: `0` (unpaid) or `1` (paid)
- Shipping calculated via `calculateShipping(country, cartItems)` using zone-based rates from `config/shipping-rates.js`
- Prices validated server-side via `validateCartPrices(cartItems, isBacker)`
- Each user should have at most ONE order. `/api/create-payment-intent` uses upsert logic: updates existing pending orders, rejects if completed, inserts only if no order exists
- `email_logs` has a FK to `orders.id` — delete email_logs before deleting an order

## Order Item Flags in `new_addons` JSON
- `isPaidKickstarterPledge: true` — pledge tier at $0 (paid backer, injected server-side)
- `isOriginalAddon: true` — KS addon or dropped backer addon (skips DB price validation)
- `isKickstarterAddon: true` — specifically a KS addon at $0 (paid backer, injected server-side)
- `isPledgeUpgrade: true` — backer upgrading to a higher tier (pays difference)
- `isDroppedBackerPledge: true` — dropped backer completing their pledge (pays full backer price)
- `isOriginalPledge: true` — dropped backer's original pledge in cart

## Kickstarter Data on Users
- `users.kickstarter_items` — JSON of items included with pledge tier (e.g. `{"ebook":1,"hardcover":1}`)
- `users.kickstarter_addons` — JSON of add-ons from KS campaign (e.g. `{"pendant":1,"audiobook_addon":1}`)
- These are NOT in sessionStorage cart for paid backers; they are display-only on frontend
- Server-side: KS addons are injected into `cartItems` at $0 in `/api/create-payment-intent` for paid backers
- Frontend: KS addons are injected into local cart in `shipping.html` for shipping calculation
- For dropped backers: dashboard.html adds KS addons to sessionStorage cart at backer prices
- KS addon key formats vary: `pendant`, `audiobook_addon`, `audiobook`, `built_env`, `"MAYA Lorebook"`, `{"quantity":1}`

## Backer Types
- `pledged_status`: `pledged`, `collected`, `dropped`
- Dropped backers are charged immediately (PaymentIntent); regular backers save card (SetupIntent)
- Indian users always charged immediately (RBI regulations)
- `is_late_pledge` flag: user pays retail instead of backer prices

## Shipping
- Shipping rates in `config/shipping-rates.js` by zone (USA, UK, EU-1/2/3, India, Australia, etc.)
- Physical addons with shipping: Built Environments, Lorebook, Paperback, Hardcover ($4-$10/zone)
- Digital/no-ship addons: Audiobook, Pendant (pendant has no shipping rate defined)
- Frontend calculates shipping in `shipping.html` via `/api/calculate-shipping`
- For paid backers, pledge + KS addons are injected into local cart before shipping API call (not in sessionStorage)

## Conventions
- Helper functions go in `utils/helpers.js` and are exported via `module.exports`
- Email sending via `services/emailService.js` (Resend API)
- Admin routes in `routes/admin.js`, prefixed with `/api/admin/`
- Standalone scripts in `utility/` connect to DB directly via `pg.Pool`
- Git push uses SSH key: `GIT_SSH_COMMAND="ssh -i ~/.ssh/id_ed25519_entermaya -o IdentitiesOnly=yes"`
